p: 3CLPro shows effective binding with three chemical compounds namely Calcium Elenolate, Monoterpene and S-Allylcysteine. Calcium Elenolate made Alkyl and hydrogen bonding with LYS 152 bond distance with 2.98 A°, hydrogen bonding with GLU 291 bond distance 3.0 A°, PHE 111 bond distance 2.60 A°. The bond energy of the complex is −7.0 kcal/mol dock pose shows in Fig. 8. S-Allylcysteine shows hydrogen bonding with ASN 112, GLN 8, ASN 150 bond distance of 3.29 A°, 2.68 A°, 2.75 A° respectively. The bond energy of the complex is −5.5 kcal/mol the 3D dock pose shows in Fig. 9. Monoterpene shows hydrogen bonding with GLY 110 with a bond distance of 2.19 A° and Alkyl bonding with LYS 152 bond energy of −6.4 kcal/mol shows in Fig. 10 (see Fig. 11).
